            "Cartels (price-fixing, market-sharing, bid-rigging) are automatically prohibited and criminally punishable",
            "Dominant position: approximately 40%+ market share. Abuse: predatory pricing, refusal to supply",
            "CMA: fines up to 10% worldwide turnover; dawn raids; merger review powers",
            "Enterprise Act 2002: criminal cartel offence — up to 5 years' imprisonment for individuals",
            "Consumer Rights Act 2015: goods must be satisfactory quality, fit for purpose, as described",
